OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: John Evans
OL,5,FAfter D-Day some of the Southern
OL,6,FRailway boats were used as hospital
OL,7,Fships and I had to go in to get an
OL,8,Forder from one of the stewards and
OL,9,Fthey were offloading American wounded
OL,10,Ffrom Omaha.
OL,12,FThere were some who didn't make it and
OL,13,Fthey were laid against the wall and
OL,14,Fall you could see was a blanket on a
OL,15,Fstretcher and a pair of boots.
OL,17,FThere were also German prisoners of
OL,18,Fwar, some of whom were wounded.
OL,20,F"And there was a British sergeant,"
OL,21,FJohn added.
