OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: John Evans
OL,5,F"He opened up the flap of his tunic
OL,6,Fpocket, took out a cigarette and gave
OL,7,Fit to the German. And I can hear that
OL,8,FGerman now - 'Danke, danke'.
OL,10,F"It's upsetting, very upsetting. I've
OL,11,Flived with it all my life and I
OL,12,Fthought 'How humane.' You didn't say
OL,13,Fwhat you saw. You didn't say anything
OL,14,Fat all.
OL,16,F"But it was a terrible sight to see
OL,17,Fall those wounded. Terrible."
